			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><span style="font-weight: bold">Why have we moved to phpBB?</span>
<br />

<br />
ezBoard was becoming to expensive, we were well over $1000 for six months.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">How can I help/donate to the running of these forums?</span>
<br />

<br />
<form action="https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr" method="post"><input type="hidden" name="cmd" value="_xclick"><input type="hidden" name="business" value="ronaldor@magecompendium.com"><input type="hidden" name="item_name" value="The Mage Compendium"><input type="hidden" name="item_number" value="themagicianstower"><input type="hidden" name="cn" value="Comments & Suggestions"><input type="hidden" name="currency_code" value="USD"><input type="hidden" name="tax" value="0"><input type="image" src="https://www.paypal.com/images/x-click-but04.gif" border="0" name="submit" alt="Donate to the running of these forums and keep them alive!"></form><span style="font-weight: bold">Do I have my old ezBoard account here?</span>
<br />

<br />
Yes we converted as many ezBoard accounts as possible, if you had an account on the old boards and posted recently it will be here.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">What is my username?</span>
<br />

<br />
Your username is exactly as it appears when you posted on ezBoard.
<br />

<br />
e.g. If your name appears on ezBoard as Bob Hoskins then your username is Bob Hoskins.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Note:</span> Spaces are allowed in usernames you don't need to use an _ . Also at present you can change your username. I will purge all in-active accounts after one month.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">What is my password?</span>
<br />

<br />
E-mail <a href="mailto:forums@zombie-jesus.com">forums@zombie-jesus.com</a> with your account name to receive your password. <span style="font-weight: bold">ONLY DO THIS IF YOUR ACCOUNT HAS BEEN TRANSFERRED</span>, if it has not please register a new account.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Note:</span> If you are unable to receive a reply with your password e-mail <a href="mailto:ronaldor@magecompendium.com">ronaldor@magecompendium.com</a> and I will deal with it myself.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Why can I not use my old password, or recover it using the find password feature?</span>
<br />

<br />
Please be aware we didn't have access to the ezBoard user database, so we don't have your e-mail addresses or old passwords. All we have is your username and a partial post count. We are making up passwords for you as you request them. But making up e-mail addresses just dosn't work.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">What do i do if I find a bug or a problem with the boards?</span>
<br />

<br />
Please post a request for technical support/help here : <a href="http://forum.magecompendium.com/tower/viewtopic.php?t=2802" target="_blank" class="postlink">http://forum.magecompendium.com/tower/viewtopic.php?t=2802</a>.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">When I edit a converted post from ezBoard it comes out as gibberish, why?</span>
<br />

<br />
Make sure you have HTML enabled, and also remove any ezCode comments.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Is there a limit to the size of my signature?</span>
<br />

<br />
Yes, at present the limit is 600 characters.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">I see you can upload an avatar to the server, how big can it be?</span>
<br />

<br />
It must be no bigger than 80 x 80 pixels and no larget than 10144 Bytes.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Can I request a custom title?</span>
<br />

<br />
If you had a custom title on the old forums please Private Message any Administrator and we will try accomodate you as soon as possible.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">I had a very large post count on the old forums can I keep it here?</span>
<br />

<br />
Please Private Message modauth for a post count restoral.
<br />

