<span style="font-weight: bold">What HTML can I use on these boards?</span>
<br />

<br />
The following HTML tags are currently allowed :
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Code:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="code">a,b,i,u,p,center,div,br,td,tr,table,h1,h2,h3,font,strike,th,img,form,small,hr,map,li</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Note:</span> If you require more HTML tags please let me know, as long as they cannot be abused they can be added, the ones currently availible are just the basic ones I thought of at the time.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">What is BBCode and how is it different from EZCodes?</span>
<br />

<br />
Many of the functions are pretty similar, and there are 'helper buttons' that appear above the text box you will write your post in. Please note that if you click on a helper button, the BBCode symbols will appear at the end of your message, not where your cursor is. For more info on the codes, check this link:
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://forum.magecompendium.com/tower/faq.php?mode=bbcode" target="_blank" class="postlink">http://forum.magecompendium.com/tower/faq.php?mode=bbcode</a>
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Why do I keep getting emails about threads i've posted in?</span>
<br />

<br />
There are two settings you can change for this. The first is in your profile section, and is called "Always notify me of replies:" If this is set to Yes, then the check box for Notify me when a reply is posted will be checked every time you post or reply. This option can be unchecked if you don't want to get emails. If you change the setting in your profile to No, then the checkbox you see when you post will be empty (can be turned on if you want to get emails on certain threads). 
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">I don't live in Great Britain, and the post times on this board confuse me. Can I change them?</span>
<br />

<br />
Sure, go to your profile and set your timezone. You can also alter the date and time format if you choose. See this link for more info on the date & time options (these are also set in your profile):
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://www.php.net/manual/en/function.date.php" target="_blank" class="postlink">http://www.php.net/manual/en/function.date.php</a>
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">What happened to the Gnogaine banner? I liked to print it out periodically and throw darts at the Gnome. How can I see this again?</span>
<br />

<br />
You may have applied a custom format to the forum. Try switching the Board Style setting in your profile to "subSilver". (At present the forums are locked to SubSilver Theme, we will allow custom themes once we are sure the forums are stable)<br />_________________<br /><br>- Ronaldor Vladimir<br>
